===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Graf had 76 people, 25 households, and 22 families. The [[population density]] was 575.2 inhabitants per square mile (222.1/km<sup>2</sup>). There were 28 housing units at an average density of 211.9 per square mile (81.8/km<sup>2</sup>).<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A31845&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A31845&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

The median age was 40.0 years. Age distribution was 28.9% under age 20, 6.6% from 20 to 24, 22.4% from 25 to 44, 21.1% from 45 to 64, and 21.1% age 65 or older. In total, 22.4% of residents were under the age of 18 and 21.1% were 65 years of age or older. For every 100 females there were 85.4 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over there were 84.4 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A31845&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

Of the 25 households, 52.0% had children under the age of 18 living with them. Of all households, 72.0% were [[Marriage|married-couple households]], 4.0% were cohabitating-couple households, 4.0% were households with a male householder and no spouse or partner present, and 20.0% were households with a female householder and no spouse or partner present. About 12.0% of households were non-families, 8.0% of all households were made up of individuals, and 4.0% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of housing units, 10.7% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

